snippet.textDisplay: I see a lot of people saying AJ would get destroyed against Wilder and that’s 100% possible cause his right hand can take out pretty much any Heavyweight, BUT nobody seems to acknowledge the fact that Wilder got rocked by 40 year old Ortiz several times, SO can he handle AJ’s power if he gets countered coming in with those swinging right hands, yeah AJ’s got a questionable chin no doubt but no one say that he isn’t easily the #2 hardest punching heavyweight in the division, adding to the fact that his boxing technique is much more solid than Wilders, he can 100% knock Wilder depending on what kind of AJ shows up on the night
